Forrest F. Dryden</link>, who was the president until 1922.</p>
<p>

<image location="left" width="150px" src="newark-2004-prudential-threat.jpg" type="thumb">
</image>
</p>
<p>

A history of The Prudential Insurance Company of America up to about 1975 is the topic of the book <it>Three Cents A Week</it>, referring to the premium paid by early policyholders.</p>
<p>

Prudential's <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../888/52888.xml">
logo</link>, The <symbol wordnetid="106806469" confidence="0.8">
<signal wordnetid="106791372" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../679/456679.xml">
Rock of Gibraltar</link></signal>
</symbol>
, is one of the most recognized corporate symbols in the world.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref>  The use of the rock began after an advertising agent passed <obstruction wordnetid="103839993" confidence="0.8">
<structure wordnetid="104341686" confidence="0.8">
<artifact wordnetid="100021939" confidence="0.8">
<blockage wordnetid="102853449" confidence="0.8">
<plug wordnetid="103967942" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../471/4391471.xml">
Laurel Hill</link></plug>
</blockage>
</artifact>
</structure>
</obstruction>
, a volcanic neck, in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../241/125241.xml">
Secaucus, New Jersey</link></village>
 on a train in the 1890s.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%223%22])">3</ref>  The slogans "Get a Piece of the Rock" and "Strength of Gibraltar" are also still quite widely associated with Prudential, though current advertising uses neither of these. <image location="right" width="100px" src="Laurel_Hill_3.jpg" type="thumb">
<caption>

Laurel Hill, the inspiration for the Rock of Gibraltar logo
</caption>
</image>
</p>
<p>

In 1999, Prudential sold its healthcare division, Prudential HealthCare, to <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../343/78343.xml">
Aetna</link></company>
 for $1 billion.</p>
<p>

